Data Collection

Data is collected from:

Databases

APIs

Files

Applications

Streaming sources

Database

A database stores structured data.

Supports CRUD operations.

SQL (Structured Query Language)

Used to interact with databases.

Schema

Logical structure of database objects.

Defines tables, columns, and relationships.

SQL Commands
DDL (Data Definition Language)

Used to define database structure.

CREATE

ALTER

DROP

TRUNCATE

Example:

CREATE TABLE student(id INT, name VARCHAR(50));

DML (Data Manipulation Language)

Used to manipulate data.

INSERT

UPDATE

DELETE

Example:

INSERT INTO student VALUES (1, 'Riya');

DQL (Data Query Language)

Used to fetch data.

SELECT

DCL (Data Control Language)

Used to control access.

GRANT

REVOKE

TCL (Transaction Control Language)

Used to manage transactions.

COMMIT

ROLLBACK

SAVEPOINT

Metadata

Data about data.

Includes table names, column names, data types.

Keys

Primary Key

Uniquely identifies records.

Foreign Key

Creates relationship between tables.

Referential Actions

ON DELETE RESTRICT

Prevents deletion of parent if child exists.

ON UPDATE CASCADE

Updates child records automatically.

Types of Constraints

NOT NULL

UNIQUE

PRIMARY KEY

FOREIGN KEY

CHECK

DELETE vs TRUNCATE vs DROP
DELETE	TRUNCATE	DROP
Removes specific rows	Removes all rows	Removes table
Can rollback	Cannot rollback	Cannot rollback
Structure remains	Structure remains	Structure removed
